<div id="review_30601530" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/30601530" />
    <a title="Jason" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1442002-jason"><img alt="Jason" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/30601530?book_show_action=true">Aug 19, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jason" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jason" href="/user/show/1442002-jason">Jason</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer30601530" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10147432895918395189"> Simply one of the best military histories out there. Mr. Ryan&apos;s last book was his masterpiece. He got the pathos and the tragedy of Market Garden right, and he lays the blame squarely where it belonged. At the feet of Field Marshal Sir Bernard Law Montgomery. The plan was flawed, and trying to run an entire corps up a road that was barely one tank wide should have been enough to kill the plan...as it was, it was not, and some 8000 British paras, along with thousands of Americans and Dutch civil</span>
  <span id="freeText10147432895918395189" style="display:none"> Simply one of the best military histories out there. Mr. Ryan's last book was his masterpiece. He got the pathos and the tragedy of Market Garden right, and he lays the blame squarely where it belonged. At the feet of Field Marshal Sir Bernard Law Montgomery. The plan was flawed, and trying to run an entire corps up a road that was barely one tank wide should have been enough to kill the plan...as it was, it was not, and some 8000 British paras, along with thousands of Americans and Dutch civilians paid the price, and instead of ending the war by Christmas, it arguably prolonged it.<br /> This book illustrates all of this in a readable style and is eminently quoteable (I mined it repeatedly for paper topics for Military Science and Military History courses, though my calling Model "Hitler's fair haired boy now that Rommel was dead" was a bit unscholarly, c'est' la vie)<br /> In short, read this book. The movie, while good, is a pale shadow to the book, and to be honest, the DVD version is horrid. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10147432895918395189" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


