        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3207769554" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11880622792180179194">This is a fantastic book if you are into non-fiction and war stories.<br/><br/>Cornelius Ryan manages to write a book that is historically accurate and researched to high standards while telling a very interesting story.<br/>Matter-of-fact explanations are intertwined with personal tales from soldiers and civilians who were in the middle of the action; including first hand interviews from high ranking allied officials and ex Wehrmacht and SS commanders, adding a very deep sense of perspective from both sides o</span>
  <span id="freeText11880622792180179194" style="display:none">This is a fantastic book if you are into non-fiction and war stories.<br /><br />Cornelius Ryan manages to write a book that is historically accurate and researched to high standards while telling a very interesting story.<br />Matter-of-fact explanations are intertwined with personal tales from soldiers and civilians who were in the middle of the action; including first hand interviews from high ranking allied officials and ex Wehrmacht and SS commanders, adding a very deep sense of perspective from both sides of the conflict.<br /><br />Operation Market-Garden itself was an ambitious assault that went wrong because of, in a big part, oversights and bad planning from the over-confident allies. It is something generally left out of the history books that everyone can benefit from learning more about.</span>
