<div id="review_1141039279" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1141039279" />
    <a title="Jarrod" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10987105-jarrod"><img alt="Jarrod" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1385871545p2/10987105.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1141039279?book_show_action=true">Jan 14, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jarrod" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jarrod" href="/user/show/10987105-jarrod">Jarrod</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audible Audio " href="/book/show/30177475-a-bridge-too-far">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10987105-jarrod?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10987105-jarrod?shelf=audio-book">audio-book</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10987105-jarrod?shelf=wwii-history">wwii-history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10987105-jarrod?shelf=military-history">military-history</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1141039279" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11981966664171775900">This tells the intimate story of Operation Market Garden during World War II from the British perspective. Written 20ish years after the war, the events were still &quot;fresh&quot; in the minds of many. The author doesn&apos;t just state what happens during the campaign, he tells the story of action from several perspectives. We see how the common soldier viewed the events, the officers, the generals, field marshals, the people in the cities and villages, the enemy and their response. You feel the anguish in </span>
  <span id="freeText11981966664171775900" style="display:none">This tells the intimate story of Operation Market Garden during World War II from the British perspective. Written 20ish years after the war, the events were still "fresh" in the minds of many. The author doesn't just state what happens during the campaign, he tells the story of action from several perspectives. We see how the common soldier viewed the events, the officers, the generals, field marshals, the people in the cities and villages, the enemy and their response. You feel the anguish in their voices as you read the struggles and failure in taking the last bridge and holding it at Arnhem. This is a story that cannot nor should not be forgotten. In the twilight of the book, I was stunned to read that more casualties came about due to this failed operation than were had during the Normandy invasion (and I consider myself somewhat well-read on the subject of WWII). I suppose there is always something to learn. I thoroughly enjoyed the book, though the person telling the story in audible had a rather drab retelling. Perhaps this was on purpose, but there was no energy in his retelling, he simply read the words it seems.<br /><br />(Stolen from another review) The best one-liner regarding Monty, though, definitely came from Ryan's interview with Prince Bernhard of the Netherlands who said:<br />“My country can never again afford the luxury of another Montgomery success.”</span>
  <a data-text-id="11981966664171775900" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


